ountry>DE</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties><assignees><assignee><addressbook><orgname>Ruhrpumpen GmbH</orgname><role>03</role><address><city>Witten</city><country>DE</country></address></addressbook></assignee></assignees><pct-or-regional-filing-data><document-id><country>WO</country><doc-number>PCT/DE12/00205</doc-number><kind>00</kind><date>20120301</date></document-id><us-371c124-date><date>20130910</date></us-371c124-date></pct-or-regional-filing-data></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A method for mounting a hydrodynamic sliding bearing of a shaft, in particular a magnetic coupling pump, wherein the hydrodynamic sliding bearing includes a bearing bushing disposed between a bearing sleeve and a bearing housing includes the steps of A coating a clamping ring on at least one of its surfaces with a friction-increasing coating, B heating the clamping ring and applying to the bearing bushing so that a pre-assembly unit is formed, and C heating the bearing housing, wherein the pre-assembly unit is inserted in the bearing housing. A double pressure bond is thus advantageously provided where a radial prevention of rotation and an axial prevention of displacement is achieved without any axial pinning as prevention from rotation and axial tensioning (e.g. L-profile ring) of the bearing bushing being required.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>